<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#b6e3b6" WIDTH="150"><B>Rule</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">Paragraph (7), immediately following the<BR ALIGN='left'/>above-mentioned paragraph, provides that<BR ALIGN='left'/>the basis for the property received for<BR ALIGN='left'/>stock in a reorganization shall be the<BR ALIGN='left'/>same as it would be in the hands of the<BR ALIGN='left'/>transferor, but only in the event that<BR ALIGN='left'/>&quot;immediately after the transfer an<BR ALIGN='left'/>interest or control in such property of<BR ALIGN='left'/>80 per centum or more remained in the<BR ALIGN='left'/>same persons or any of them.&quot; If such<BR ALIGN='left'/>interest or control did not remain in<BR ALIGN='left'/>such hands, then, of course, the general<BR ALIGN='left'/>rule applied, to wit, cost.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>]
