  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#add8ff" WIDTH="150"><B>Analysis</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">Section 112(d) (1) makes this section<BR ALIGN='left'/>applicable, even though property or<BR ALIGN='left'/>money, in addition to stock, be<BR ALIGN='left'/>exchanged for other 268*268 property,<BR ALIGN='left'/>provided such property or money be<BR ALIGN='left'/>distributed in pursuance to the plan of<BR ALIGN='left'/>reorganization. The transaction here<BR ALIGN='left'/>clearly was a reorganization, and the<BR ALIGN='left'/>money received by the plaintiff&#x27;s<BR ALIGN='left'/>predecessors was distributed by them<BR ALIGN='left'/>pursuant to the plan of reorganization,<BR ALIGN='left'/>and the above-quoted sections,<BR ALIGN='left'/>therefore, are applicable.</TD></TR>
